article.headline: Colgate 34, Dartmouth 15
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Jordan McCord ran for 212 yards and two touchdowns to lead Colgate to a 34-15 win over Dartmouth on Saturday. The Raiders (3-0) held Dartmouth to 26 yards rushing. The Big Green, who played their first game of the season, went 2 of 11 on third down. Colgate's Greg Sullivan was 12 of 19 for 172 yards and one touchdown. Sullivan also had 51 yards rushing on 10 carries and two touchdowns. Pat Simmonds caught three passes for 64 yards for the Raiders, who have beaten Dartmouth 10 of the last 11 times. Colgate also held the Big Green to 173 yards on offense. Alex Jenny threw for 147 yards on 11 of 28 for Dartmouth.
